			<div class="content" id="post-content-2357735">
									

<p>I loved the second scene, probably because its closer to realism and easier to get absorbed in.</p>
<p>That being said, each scene is done wonderfully, and any possible points where you could have depicted something tastelessly, you don't and make it poignant and meaningful and powerful. The imagery here is good, and most of the characters I can get invested in and follow, or buy. Plus, it helps that it involves a mythos related to one of my favorite SCPs on the site (1440), which definitely helps to swallow this in that regard! I can dig this.</p>

							</div>

								
					
