															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anaxagoras" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1019930); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1019930&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203968" alt="Anaxagoras" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1019930)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/anaxagoras" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1019930); return false;" >Anaxagoras</a></span> <span class="odate time_1439627405 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Aug 2015 08:30</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2357910">
									

<p>Though that should indeed be &quot;leaches&quot;, I don't think there's actually a tense disagreement. If I'm reading that sentence right, it's actually a simile — how did Death enter the town? As poison enters a well. That said, it's not immediately clear that that is a simile rather than just describing an event happening at the same time as Death enters the village, so perhaps that should be reworded.</p>

							</div>

								
					
